WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:14.573 --> 00:16.291
[Scooby chomps and giggles]

00:21.173 --> 00:24.643
[Rock version of <i>Scooby Doo</i> theme song]

00:42.813 --> 00:45.281
[Suspenseful instrumental music]

00:45.973 --> 00:47.292
[Ghost cackles]

00:47.373 --> 00:48.362
DAPHNE: Shaggy!

00:50.653 --> 00:54.931
DAPHNE: Now I really have a wedgie.
Fred! Velma!

00:55.213 --> 00:58.569
Can you guys hurry it up?
This ghost keeps grabbing...

00:58.653 --> 00:59.642
[Daphne screams]

01:00.053 --> 01:01.372
DAPHNE: Please!

01:01.653 --> 01:02.847
Jinkies!

01:03.573 --> 01:04.244
Fred.

01:04.492 --> 01:05.812
VELMA: <i>Come in, Fred. </i>

01:06.253 --> 01:09.450
VELMA: <i>Fred. Can you hear me? </i>
FRED: Fredster here, Velms.

01:09.933 --> 01:13.243
VELMA: <i>Shockingly, Daphne's</i>
<i>been captured again. That's okay. </i>

01:13.333 --> 01:15.927
When the Luna Ghost
rounds the corner with Daphne...

01:16.053 --> 01:18.408
<i>... Shaggy and Scooby</i>
<i>will pop out of the barrel... </i>

01:18.493 --> 01:22.406
And you'll activate the conveyor belt,
spilling the vat of oil onto the floor.

01:24.253 --> 01:25.572
VELMA: <i>Just remember my plan. </i>

01:26.253 --> 01:29.051
SHAGGY: Like, chill out, Scooby Doo.
Stop shaking.

01:29.213 --> 01:31.090
SCOOBY: Hey! That's you.

01:31.173 --> 01:33.129
SHAGGY: Right. It's me. Sorry!

01:44.053 --> 01:45.122
Boo!

01:45.213 --> 01:47.283
[Scooby screams]

01:47.413 --> 01:50.052
[Whispers] Scooby Doo.
What are you doing, man?

01:50.613 --> 01:52.126
SHAGGY: Like, this is no time...

01:55.413 --> 01:59.008
Oh, boy. Like, there's a ghost
right behind me, isn't there?

01:59.253 --> 02:00.925
[Scooby grunts assent]

02:04.773 --> 02:06.252
Run!

02:15.093 --> 02:16.651
SCOOBY: Run! Go!

02:16.733 --> 02:18.769
SHAGGY: I'm trying, buddy!

02:18.853 --> 02:19.842
[Scooby screams]

02:20.853 --> 02:22.969
[Yells] Fred, now!

02:24.613 --> 02:26.683
FRED: I got him.
SCOOBY: Look out!

02:42.413 --> 02:44.210
FRED: Sorry, Velma.
VELMA: I know, Fred.

02:44.813 --> 02:46.087
SHAGGY: Where's the ghost?

02:46.173 --> 02:49.529
He's right behind us! Skateboard!

02:49.613 --> 02:51.092
[Shaggy yells]

03:03.173 --> 03:04.652
[Ghost cackles]

03:05.293 --> 03:06.806
Is he still after us, Scoob?

03:08.613 --> 03:09.932
Banzai!

03:15.133 --> 03:15.929
Zoinks!

03:16.493 --> 03:17.767
SHAGGY: Grab the hook!

03:17.853 --> 03:19.491
SCOOBY: Hold on, Shaggy!

03:34.813 --> 03:36.246
VELMA: Daphne? Are you okay?

03:38.573 --> 03:41.485
I'm so over this
'<i>'</i> damsel in distress'<i>'</i> nonsense.

03:42.013 --> 03:43.128
Where's Shagster?

03:44.973 --> 03:47.407
- Like, I'm right here, man.
- Me, too.

03:47.493 --> 03:51.964
Scoob, that was fun. Let's grab another
skateboard and, like, do it again.

03:52.493 --> 03:53.972
[Scooby giggles]

03:54.053 --> 03:55.042
[Fred gasps]

03:57.933 --> 03:59.412
[Tires screech]

04:02.613 --> 04:06.083
[Rock 'n' roll music]

04:08.173 --> 04:10.050
[Fans scream]

04:11.733 --> 04:13.371
FRED: There you go.

04:13.453 --> 04:15.171
And one for you.

04:15.813 --> 04:16.928
Good-looking guy.

04:17.093 --> 04:18.970
FRED: All right, nice to see you.

04:19.053 --> 04:20.884
Thank you so much for saving the factory.

04:20.973 --> 04:22.725
REPORTER: Any comments?
FRED: It's my job.

04:22.813 --> 04:24.929
This is a victory
for any celebrity who wants...

04:25.013 --> 04:27.732
...to make a quality,
ecologically-friendly action figure.

04:27.813 --> 04:29.724
Fred, what's the secret of your success?

04:30.053 --> 04:33.329
Teamwork.
I do a tremendous amount of teamwork...

04:33.573 --> 04:35.803
...and I always have a plan. Come on.

04:35.893 --> 04:37.724
Yeah, my plan.

04:37.893 --> 04:42.842
FRED: I knew there never was a phantom.
The Luna Ghost is, in fact...

04:45.773 --> 04:47.525
ALL: Old Man Smithers?

04:47.613 --> 04:49.012
The creepy janitor?

04:49.093 --> 04:51.527
He wanted revenge
after you refused to go out with him.

04:51.613 --> 04:52.841
How could you, Pamela?

04:53.373 --> 04:56.524
I am a lover boy
of George Clooneyan proportions.

04:56.613 --> 04:58.683
REPORTER: Fred,
how was the ghost able to fly?

04:58.773 --> 05:00.411
VELMA: I can answer that.

05:00.493 --> 05:01.642
VELMA: Watch.

05:04.213 --> 05:07.967
These balloons fill with a highly potent
helium synthesis...

05:08.813 --> 05:10.292
...giving the Luna Ghost...

05:11.653 --> 05:13.245
...his weightless appearance.

05:15.293 --> 05:19.206
I would have gotten away with it too,
if it weren't for you meddling kids...

05:19.293 --> 05:20.965
...and your dumb dog!

05:21.493 --> 05:23.165
I'll get you for this!

05:23.253 --> 05:24.891
[Howls] Scooby Dooby Doo!

05:28.653 --> 05:30.325
[lndistinct chatter]

05:31.813 --> 05:34.247
VELMA: I can't believe you took credit
for my plan again.

05:34.333 --> 05:37.803
DAPHNE: Some plan.
That ghost pawed me for an hour and a half.

05:37.893 --> 05:40.123
FRED: Daph, it's not our fault
you always get kidnapped.

05:40.213 --> 05:44.001
I do not always get kidnapped.
I can't believe you'd say that to me.

05:44.333 --> 05:45.482
Please.

05:45.573 --> 05:47.325
<i>You come with your own ransom note. </i>

05:48.773 --> 05:51.048
- My glasses!
- Who's helpless now?

05:51.493 --> 05:53.131
I'm going to kill you, Daphne!

05:53.493 --> 05:54.482
[Fred yelps]

05:54.853 --> 05:55.888
Watch the ascot!

05:56.173 --> 05:57.447
SHAGGY: You guys, look.

05:57.893 --> 06:00.726
I know I'm just the dude
that carries the bags...

06:00.813 --> 06:03.964
...but it seems to me we all play
an important part in this group.

06:04.133 --> 06:07.284
I mean, we're just like a big,
delicious banana split.

06:07.853 --> 06:10.367
Fred, you're the big banana.

06:11.253 --> 06:15.246
Daph, you're the pastrami and bubble gum
flavored ice cream, and Velma...

06:15.333 --> 06:18.609
...you're the sweet and sour mustard sauce
that goes on top.

06:20.213 --> 06:22.443
That sounds pretty good, doesn't it?

06:22.813 --> 06:24.132
You know what, Shaggy?

06:24.693 --> 06:26.923
You've really put it into perspective for me.

06:27.773 --> 06:28.967
Thanks.

06:30.013 --> 06:31.048
I quit.

06:32.813 --> 06:33.802
No.

06:34.413 --> 06:35.448
No way.

06:35.733 --> 06:36.927
<i>You can't quit. </i>

06:37.613 --> 06:39.763
I was going to quit in, like, two seconds.

06:39.853 --> 06:43.209
Now everyone is going to totally think
I copied off the smart girl.

06:43.293 --> 06:45.011
Now, wait a minute!

06:47.293 --> 06:48.328
Maybe I quit.

06:51.333 --> 06:52.607
I do.

06:52.933 --> 06:54.366
Yeah, I quit!

06:55.373 --> 06:56.408
I'm outta here.

06:58.933 --> 06:59.968
Good riddance.

07:00.533 --> 07:02.205
Don't... No! Don't go!

07:02.733 --> 07:04.485
SHAGGY: Come on, you guys, don't do this!

07:06.053 --> 07:07.202
Please, don't go.

07:11.013 --> 07:12.162
Do I quit?

07:13.453 --> 07:14.852
No, Scoob...

07:15.173 --> 07:16.447
...friends don't quit.

07:19.573 --> 07:22.883
SHAGGY: <i>Well, it looks like it's just you</i>
<i>and me for a while, buddy, old pal. </i>

07:22.973 --> 07:24.122
SCOOBY: <i>What now, Shaggy? </i>

07:24.853 --> 07:27.845
SHAGGY: <i>I guess we'll all just do</i>
<i>what we do best, Scoob. </i>

07:33.293 --> 07:35.363
[Lively reggae music]

07:37.493 --> 07:39.165
SHAGGY: This is primo.

07:40.093 --> 07:41.162
<i>Oh, man. </i>

07:41.453 --> 07:43.011
<i>Talk about toasted. </i>

07:45.333 --> 07:48.370
The only thing I like better
than an eggplant burger...

07:48.773 --> 07:52.368
...is a chocolate-covered eggplant burger.

07:52.453 --> 07:53.647
With hot sauce.

07:56.933 --> 08:00.243
Yeah. Just another beautiful day
in paradise.

08:02.053 --> 08:05.682
ISLAND EMISSARY: I'm looking for a
Mr. Rogers and a Mr. Doo, the detectives?

08:05.773 --> 08:09.561
Like, it's probably somebody else looking
for us to solve some terrifying mystery.

08:09.653 --> 08:10.642
Nobody home.

08:11.173 --> 08:13.733
Quick, Scoob-o.
Grab the food-o, let's scram-o.

08:13.973 --> 08:16.362
ISLAND EMISSARY: I'm looking for a Mr.
Rogers and Mr. Doo.

08:20.973 --> 08:22.008
SHAGGY: Let's go.

08:23.813 --> 08:24.962
I'm sorry, dude.

08:25.973 --> 08:29.852
Look, I'd love to help you out.
You look like a really nice guy.

08:30.013 --> 08:31.924
It's just we're not detectives anymore.

08:32.013 --> 08:35.528
I've been sent by my employer,
Mr. Emile Mondavarious, to invite you...

08:35.613 --> 08:37.888
...to his world-famous amusement park,
Spooky Island.

08:37.972 --> 08:42.011
We don't go near any place with spooky,
haunted, forbidden, or creepy in the name.

08:42.253 --> 08:43.207
Or hydrocolonic.

08:43.293 --> 08:46.569
Right, or hydrocolonic,
but that's for a whole different reason.

08:46.893 --> 08:49.532
Mr. Mondavarious would like you
to solve a mystery.

08:49.813 --> 08:52.168
He'll pay you a fee of $10,000.

08:52.253 --> 08:55.689
It's just,
materialism's not really our bag, man.

08:55.813 --> 08:57.451
- He can provide free airfare.
- No, thanks.

08:57.533 --> 08:59.251
- Room and board.
- No, thanks.

08:59.333 --> 09:01.210
And all you can eat.

09:03.253 --> 09:04.481
SCOOBY: '<i>'</i> All you can eat? '<i>'</i>

09:20.173 --> 09:22.129
- Fred?
- Velma?

09:22.893 --> 09:24.246
Are you going this way?

09:30.133 --> 09:31.248
How have you...

09:31.333 --> 09:32.322
Been?

09:32.453 --> 09:33.203
Yeah.

09:33.573 --> 09:37.646
Great! Great. I'm on the lecture circuit
with my new book.

09:38.333 --> 09:40.801
'<i>'Fred on Fred: The Many Faces of Me</i>. '<i>'</i>

09:41.293 --> 09:42.726
Jinkies, that's impressive.

09:43.973 --> 09:44.928
And yourself?

09:45.013 --> 09:49.609
I've been working at NASA, developing
hydro-powered missile defense systems.

09:49.693 --> 09:52.765
But, more importantly,
I'm on a journey of self-discovery.

09:52.853 --> 09:53.888
NASA, huh?

09:53.973 --> 09:57.648
ANNOUNCER: <i>Charter service to Spooky</i>
<i>Island will begin boarding momentarily. </i>

09:58.093 --> 10:00.766
DAPHNE: What do you mean,
I can't have seven carry-on bags?

10:00.853 --> 10:02.889
DAPHNE: That is so economy.
VELMA: Crap.

10:04.933 --> 10:06.127
Oh, no.

10:06.453 --> 10:07.966
I'm not talking to you guys.

10:12.733 --> 10:14.086
What are you doing here?

10:14.173 --> 10:15.401
VELMA: Isn't it obvious?

10:15.493 --> 10:18.371
We all received the same letter
from one Emile Mondavarious...

10:18.693 --> 10:20.729
...the reclusive owner of Spooky Island.

10:21.213 --> 10:25.445
Unfair! I was going to solve the mystery
all by myself, for the first time ever.

10:25.533 --> 10:27.330
How are you going to save yourself
when you get caught?

10:27.413 --> 10:28.448
DAPHNE: I'm a black belt.

10:28.533 --> 10:31.366
I've transformed my body
into a dangerous weapon.

10:33.893 --> 10:34.928
It's true.

10:35.013 --> 10:39.052
Far out. I guess we're, like, all going
to Spooky Island, man.

10:39.613 --> 10:41.126
Hey, where's Scooby?

10:41.213 --> 10:44.091
[Funky rap music]

10:45.173 --> 10:46.572
[Whistles and catcalls]

10:47.373 --> 10:48.488
Hello.

10:51.693 --> 10:54.161
They don't allow big dogs on the plane.

10:58.293 --> 11:00.011
You've got to be kidding.

11:00.093 --> 11:02.084
No one is stupid enough to believe that.

11:03.133 --> 11:04.452
Who's the ugly old broad?

11:07.613 --> 11:08.841
Say hello to Grandma.

11:08.933 --> 11:12.243
ANNOUNCER:
<i>Flight 3774 to Spooky Island, now boarding. </i>

11:12.333 --> 11:14.893
Listen, I wouldn't have agreed to come
if I knew...

11:14.973 --> 11:17.203
Wait, just think about it for one minute.

11:18.253 --> 11:19.845
Mystery Inc reunites.

11:20.333 --> 11:22.801
<i>We'll be a team again. </i>
<i>Just like the old days. </i>

11:22.973 --> 11:24.008
<i>So, come on, gang. </i>

11:24.293 --> 11:28.571
Let's do that thing where we put
our hands in, lift them up, and we go...

11:29.413 --> 11:30.402
[Shaggy cheers]

11:30.693 --> 11:32.251
Only if Fred and Velma do it.

11:35.813 --> 11:37.212
People are watching, Shag.

11:42.453 --> 11:44.921
[Soft piano music plays]

11:45.493 --> 11:46.482
[Scooby cheers]

11:47.573 --> 11:48.972
Yeah, Scoob! Whoo-hoo!

11:49.813 --> 11:50.848
Come on, buddy.

11:52.373 --> 11:55.046
[Loud rock 'n' roll music]

12:10.613 --> 12:12.968
Now, that is a beautiful work of art, Scoob.

12:16.653 --> 12:18.530
[Soft dreamlike music]

12:30.773 --> 12:33.241
Would you mind me
taking a seat there next to...

12:34.733 --> 12:38.521
To my Grandma? That's my grandma.
Hi, Grandma. Like, no.

12:40.893 --> 12:42.292
- Let me just...
- Thanks.

12:42.373 --> 12:43.692
You're welcome.

12:46.573 --> 12:47.892
Bless you.

12:48.933 --> 12:53.723
I'm sorry. My allergies are...
Well, it's usually only dogs that do it.

12:56.973 --> 12:58.292
Maybe I'd better move.

12:58.573 --> 12:59.767
No. Wait.

12:59.853 --> 13:02.651
It's probably just my grandma's perfume.

13:03.253 --> 13:08.008
Yeah, even I sometimes get a little allergic,
you know. Jeez. Look.

13:09.213 --> 13:13.286
I'm pretty sure Grandma wants to go back
and visit with her old pal, Velma.

13:13.453 --> 13:14.442
Right, Grandma?

13:15.253 --> 13:16.288
Okay.

13:22.173 --> 13:26.086
Boy, oh, boy, those sure do look
like Scooby Snacks.

13:26.893 --> 13:28.326
I know they're for dogs...

13:29.013 --> 13:31.686
...but they're 100 percent vegetarian
and I love them.

13:32.173 --> 13:33.367
Me, too!

13:33.653 --> 13:37.123
Far out. I have never met another person
who loves Scooby Snacks.

13:37.213 --> 13:38.248
Me neither.

13:38.333 --> 13:39.766
I'm Mary Jane.

13:40.893 --> 13:42.963
SHAGGY: That is my favorite name.
MARY JANE: Really?

13:43.053 --> 13:44.486
- Yeah.
- No way.

13:50.293 --> 13:51.328
Hello.

13:59.853 --> 14:02.128
[Scooby barks loudly]

14:03.013 --> 14:04.048
Grandma?

14:04.133 --> 14:06.886
Velma, it's simple behavior modification.

14:06.973 --> 14:11.763
To cause a dog to discontinue any action,
simply flick it on the nose. Observe.

14:15.893 --> 14:16.962
See?

14:21.573 --> 14:25.452
SHAGGY: <i>Sit, Grandma! Bad Grandma! </i>
<i>Don't eat the kitty! </i>

14:28.053 --> 14:30.726
[Tribal instrumental music]

14:32.653 --> 14:35.247
EMILE: <i>Welcome to Spooky Island... </i>

14:35.333 --> 14:39.565
<i>... the frightfully popular spring break spot</i>
<i>for college students! </i>

14:39.653 --> 14:41.769
<i>Catch our Electrical Torture Parade... </i>

14:41.853 --> 14:44.321
<i>... lt's a Dead World After All... </i>

14:44.413 --> 14:46.973
<i>... and the world-famous Splatter Horn. </i>

14:48.973 --> 14:52.727
<i>Scooby Doo and the rest of Mystery Inc! </i>

14:52.813 --> 14:54.883
<i>It's marvelous to see you. </i>

14:56.133 --> 14:59.170
<i>I'm so sorry. </i>

15:00.453 --> 15:01.772
Thank goodness.

15:01.853 --> 15:05.812
Sorry. It's a new toy.
I'm just sort of getting up to speed with it.

15:05.893 --> 15:08.123
EMILE: Welcome.
DAPHNE: Thank goodness.

15:08.493 --> 15:11.053
I was afraid
I'd have to lug those up to the hotel.

15:11.133 --> 15:15.445
But that's what Spooky Island's all about,
realizing your worst fears.

15:15.853 --> 15:17.764
EMILE: I'm Emile Mondavarious...

15:18.053 --> 15:20.408
...the owner of this amusement park.

15:20.493 --> 15:21.528
VELMA: You seem less...

15:22.133 --> 15:24.203
- Spooky!
- Then we'd have guessed.

15:25.413 --> 15:27.529
I can be pretty spooky when called upon.

15:27.613 --> 15:28.887
EMILE: Oh, I can go...

15:28.973 --> 15:29.962
[Emile snarls]

15:30.693 --> 15:32.524
And claws and everything.

15:33.693 --> 15:36.161
You wouldn't want to run into me
in a dark alley.

15:36.733 --> 15:38.644
So you're the one who brought us here?

15:38.813 --> 15:39.848
No.

15:40.093 --> 15:44.769
No, what brought you here was
your insatiable appetite for a juicy mystery.

15:46.253 --> 15:49.370
The truth is, Mr. Mondavarious,
Mystery Inc is broken up.

15:49.453 --> 15:51.648
That's the beauty of something broken.

15:51.733 --> 15:54.645
It can be fixed, and therein lies its potential.

15:54.973 --> 15:57.441
And I need you to fix Spooky Island.

15:57.533 --> 15:59.285
VELMA: What's the problem?

15:59.373 --> 16:02.570
EMILE: I believe somebody
is casting a spell on the students.

16:03.693 --> 16:05.729
EMILE: Now listen and look around.

16:06.253 --> 16:09.962
<i>Can you notice any difference between</i>
<i>those arriving and those departing? </i>

16:10.053 --> 16:12.772
DAPHNE: They look like sober,
well-behaved college kids.

16:12.853 --> 16:15.413
EMILE: Precisely. And they didn't
before they came.

16:15.853 --> 16:19.163
They've changed.
In other words, a magic spell.

16:19.533 --> 16:22.047
BRAD: Carol! How was the Island?

16:22.933 --> 16:24.491
Are you tricking on me?

16:26.413 --> 16:30.486
It's me, Brad. We've known each other
since we were, like, three.

16:30.573 --> 16:32.052
CAROL: Back off my grille!

16:33.493 --> 16:34.812
BRAD: What are you doing?

16:46.133 --> 16:47.452
I'm terrified.

16:47.533 --> 16:49.842
<i>The young people</i>
<i>that come off that barge... </i>

16:49.933 --> 16:54.165
...the people I love the most,
they're in danger.

16:54.613 --> 16:56.569
I will solve this one first.

16:56.653 --> 16:58.928
FRED: Not before I solve it first.
EMILE: Well done.

16:59.013 --> 17:03.086
You guys are going to look like total idiots
when you're captured and I save you.

17:03.493 --> 17:04.972
Thank you. Marvelous.

17:05.333 --> 17:08.769
EMILE: Maybe we can celebrate later
by having a little Spookapalooza.

17:08.853 --> 17:11.002
Spookapalooza?

17:13.333 --> 17:14.652
[Ominous tribal drums]

17:14.733 --> 17:18.964
So, you haven't noticed anything unusual
since you've started working here?

17:19.813 --> 17:21.565
<i>Any weirdoes running around? </i>

17:22.252 --> 17:23.606
SKELETON: No.

17:24.252 --> 17:26.050
[Ominous tribal chanting]

17:41.693 --> 17:44.651
N'GOO: Welcome, dear victims!

17:44.933 --> 17:48.209
My name is N'Goo Tauna...

17:48.853 --> 17:52.562
...and this is my evil best pal, Zarkos.

17:53.293 --> 17:57.764
You may recognize him from Telemundo
as the famous, masked wrestler...

17:58.293 --> 17:59.442
<i>... Zarkos. </i>

17:59.533 --> 18:01.489
<i>This enchanted island... </i>

18:01.773 --> 18:05.129
<i>... is a thoroughfare</i>
<i>to the supernatural realm. </i>

18:06.413 --> 18:08.643
<i>For centuries it was home to creatures... </i>

18:08.733 --> 18:11.566
<i>... who lived on the island, undisturbed. </i>

18:14.453 --> 18:15.681
<i>But then... </i>

18:16.213 --> 18:17.931
...10 years ago...

18:18.373 --> 18:21.365
<i>... Emile Mondavarious... </i>

18:21.973 --> 18:27.286
<i>... antagonized these ancient beings</i>
<i>by building a theme park here. </i>

18:30.493 --> 18:33.087
The creatures are furious, my friends...

18:34.693 --> 18:36.092
...and I assure you...

18:36.773 --> 18:38.764
...while you party...

18:39.533 --> 18:42.001
...they plot their...

18:42.733 --> 18:43.848
...revenge!

18:51.053 --> 18:53.123
N'GOO: Do my friends frighten you?

18:56.693 --> 19:00.242
They would
if it weren't for the holographic projectors...

19:01.253 --> 19:04.484
...there, and there, and there.

19:06.573 --> 19:08.325
What a smart little one.

19:13.053 --> 19:14.725
[Spooky rap music]

19:21.613 --> 19:23.524
Hello. Dead Mike's.

19:25.533 --> 19:27.410
BARTENDER: We got a Mr. Doo here?

19:27.613 --> 19:29.331
<i>I got a call for a Mr. Doo. </i>

19:30.653 --> 19:31.847
Melvin Doo?

19:31.933 --> 19:33.764
No, Scooby.

19:36.613 --> 19:37.648
Hello.

19:37.733 --> 19:41.009
MAN: <i>Got a bag of hamburgers here... </i>

19:41.093 --> 19:42.572
<i>... for you. </i>

19:42.693 --> 19:46.049
<i>Just walk into the dark, </i>
<i>shadowy part of the forest... </i>

19:46.213 --> 19:48.488
<i>... where no one can see you. </i>

19:49.173 --> 19:50.447
Okay.

19:54.733 --> 19:57.725
SHAGGY: Want a stuffed thingy?
MARY JANE: Nobody can win at those.

19:57.813 --> 19:59.724
SHAGGY: Fred says it's a worthless talent.

19:59.813 --> 20:02.043
That I should've learned French instead.

20:02.133 --> 20:06.251
But, I say you don't need to know what
'<i>'Voulez-vous coucher avec moi</i>'<i>'</i> means...

20:06.333 --> 20:08.130
SHAGGY: to love that song.

20:08.973 --> 20:12.329
I think being good at crane machine
is way cooler than French.

20:14.813 --> 20:15.962
<i>Voilà</i>.

20:16.693 --> 20:20.288
Nobody's ever given me a stuffed,
dismembered head before.

20:23.173 --> 20:25.164
[Shouting and chanting]

20:34.173 --> 20:36.243
[Chanting and grunting]

20:47.933 --> 20:49.002
Excuse me.

20:50.053 --> 20:51.202
What are you doing?

20:51.293 --> 20:53.807
Now I have to start my voodoo ritual
all over again!

20:53.893 --> 20:57.090
- Voodoo ritual?
- Yes. I was about to sacrifice this chicken.

20:57.413 --> 21:00.962
DAPHNE: But that chicken's not alive.
VOODOO MAN: I know that, smart girl.

21:01.053 --> 21:03.442
You figured it out
when you saw it didn't have a head?

21:03.533 --> 21:04.932
<i>What do you want? </i>

21:05.013 --> 21:07.163
Why are you all up
in my voodoo ritual space?

21:07.253 --> 21:11.007
I'm looking for clues as to who's behind
the strange behavior of the students.

21:12.453 --> 21:16.128
Well, here's a clue. Purple is a fall color.
It's the middle of May!

21:17.053 --> 21:18.008
Pardon?

21:18.093 --> 21:20.766
Do yourself a favor and get off this island.
Go home.

21:20.853 --> 21:24.687
Go home before evil befalls your little,
skinny, aerobicized booty.

21:24.773 --> 21:26.604
VOODOO MAN: And whatever you do...

21:26.693 --> 21:28.763
...do not, I repeat...

21:28.853 --> 21:32.607
<i>... do not go into that Spooky Island castle. </i>

21:34.333 --> 21:37.848
- You want me to go up to that castle.
- Didn't you just hear what I said?

21:37.933 --> 21:41.209
But you're scary and you knew
I'd do the opposite of what you said.

21:41.293 --> 21:43.932
So you told me not to go,
so I'd go up to that castle...

21:44.013 --> 21:46.811
...where you've set a trap to capture me.

21:47.253 --> 21:48.527
Unless...

21:48.733 --> 21:52.408
...you knew I'd figure it out, so you told me
not to go up to the castle...

21:52.493 --> 21:56.486
...so I'd think you wanted me to go,
so I wouldn't go, like you didn't want me to.

21:56.893 --> 21:59.851
DAPHNE: I'll find out what you're hiding
in that castle. You watch.

22:01.573 --> 22:03.245
What in the world?

22:05.413 --> 22:06.562
Hamburgers...

22:06.653 --> 22:08.405
<i>... oh, where are you? </i>

22:19.333 --> 22:20.686
SCOOBY: Hamburgers.

22:23.093 --> 22:24.367
Thank you.

22:27.253 --> 22:29.323
[Ghoul murmurs]

22:44.053 --> 22:45.247
[Ghoul shrieks]

22:46.893 --> 22:49.361
Shaggy, help me!

23:09.813 --> 23:11.292
This has been really nice.

23:11.373 --> 23:13.011
SCOOBY: [Yells] Help!

23:15.773 --> 23:17.286
Monster!

23:18.053 --> 23:19.566
A monster?

23:25.173 --> 23:27.812
Scooby Doo!
Like, quit goofing around, man.

23:27.893 --> 23:29.246
MARY JANE: I guess I should go.

23:33.093 --> 23:34.492
'Bye, Scooby.

23:38.053 --> 23:39.372
Bless you.

23:44.373 --> 23:45.886
Shaggy, Scooby.

23:48.893 --> 23:50.485
[Mysterious howling]

23:52.173 --> 23:53.242
No way.

23:53.653 --> 23:54.927
Shaggy.

23:55.253 --> 23:58.006
SHAGGY: Scoob and me don't do castles.
DAPHNE: Why not?

23:58.093 --> 24:02.928
Paintings with eyes watching you,
suits of armor you think is a statue...

24:03.013 --> 24:07.165
...but there's a guy inside who follows you
every time you turn around.

24:07.453 --> 24:09.808
DAPHNE: How many times has it happened?
SHAGGY: Twelve.

24:10.093 --> 24:12.243
SHAGGY: We're not gonna do it.
SCOOBY: That's right.

24:13.853 --> 24:14.683
Scooby?

24:17.733 --> 24:19.212
DAPHNE: Did you hurt your paw?

24:19.853 --> 24:22.572
- Would you do it for a Scooby Snack?
- Oh, boy!

24:24.693 --> 24:25.887
You'll be fearless?

24:26.413 --> 24:27.448
Fearless?

24:33.853 --> 24:36.731
Hong Kong Fuey,
watch the fists of fury, would you, buddy!

24:36.813 --> 24:37.848
Here you go.

24:39.173 --> 24:40.083
Thank you.

24:40.173 --> 24:43.688
There's plenty more where that came from.
Let's go before someone sees.

24:43.773 --> 24:44.762
SCOOBY: Okay.

24:46.973 --> 24:49.441
You are not going to stay out here alone,
are you?

24:49.813 --> 24:51.007
No, thank you.

24:51.853 --> 24:54.321
[Suspenseful instrumental music]

25:05.173 --> 25:08.245
SHAGGY: This place is like, <i>über</i> creepy.

25:08.533 --> 25:10.569
SCOOBY: Yeah, <i>über</i> creepy.

25:10.653 --> 25:12.848
DAPHNE: The only thing missing
is a mindless zombie.

25:13.693 --> 25:14.967
[Door bursts open]

25:18.413 --> 25:19.641
DAPHNE: Fred, get back.

25:20.653 --> 25:22.962
I found this place. I call dibs on its clues.

25:23.173 --> 25:24.845
I've already found some clues.

25:24.933 --> 25:26.082
What?

25:26.173 --> 25:29.882
I followed some weird footprints
up here and it might be dangerous for you.

25:30.213 --> 25:31.612
If anyone messes with me...

25:31.693 --> 25:35.003
...l'll just open a can of 2000-year-old
Chinese whup-ass on them.

25:37.973 --> 25:38.644
Velma!

25:38.933 --> 25:40.252
What are you doing here?

25:40.333 --> 25:42.893
VELMA: This ride was closed
due to dangerous construction.

25:43.373 --> 25:45.887
The most likely place
to hatch an insidious plan...

25:46.213 --> 25:48.932
...and I wanted to scare the patootie
out of Daphne.

25:49.173 --> 25:53.166
Well, since we're all together,
let's split up and look for more clues.

25:53.573 --> 25:55.450
- Daphne, you and I...
- Typical.

25:55.813 --> 25:56.484
What?

25:56.573 --> 26:00.532
Oh, nothing.
I was always picked last for the teams.

26:00.613 --> 26:01.728
FRED: Okay.

26:02.293 --> 26:04.124
Daphne, exit through the entrance.

26:04.453 --> 26:07.092
Velma and I will enter here
through the exit there.

26:07.373 --> 26:08.692
And Shaggy and Scooby...

26:10.853 --> 26:12.366
...do whatever you guys do.

26:16.813 --> 26:18.007
[Door creaking open]

26:24.933 --> 26:26.127
[Distant cackling]

26:26.733 --> 26:28.803
[Mystical instrumental music]

26:29.213 --> 26:31.044
Look at this, Scoob.

26:31.293 --> 26:33.488
SHAGGY: It's like a medieval Sizzler.

26:33.813 --> 26:37.965
Pinch me, I'm in... It's an expression, Scoob.

26:38.493 --> 26:39.642
Sorry.

26:47.053 --> 26:48.532
[Daphne grunts]

26:55.693 --> 26:59.129
FRED: Hey, Velma, I never meant to,
well, you know...

26:59.213 --> 27:00.407
...pick you last.

27:00.733 --> 27:03.770
Don't worry about it, Fred. I know you.

27:03.893 --> 27:05.849
All you care about are swimsuit models.

27:05.933 --> 27:10.882
No! Look, I'm a man of substance.
Dorky chicks like you turn me on, too.

27:16.093 --> 27:17.492
That's a compliment.

27:37.653 --> 27:39.052
Yes!

27:47.133 --> 27:50.011
Oh, yeah! Oh, yeah! Uh-huh!

27:54.133 --> 27:56.567
PHANTOM: <i>And now for our dinner show! </i>

27:58.533 --> 28:00.922
[Evil cackling and laughing]

28:05.053 --> 28:06.042
VELMA: Watch out!

28:10.533 --> 28:13.331
SHAGGY: I got a bad feeling about this.
SCOOBY: Me, too.

28:13.413 --> 28:15.927
PHANTOM: <i>And now for the main course: </i>

28:16.013 --> 28:17.287
<i>You! </i>

28:19.493 --> 28:21.961
<i>Feast on this! </i>

28:31.053 --> 28:32.042
VELMA: Jinkies!

28:32.653 --> 28:34.006
VELMA: They're moving toward us.

28:37.533 --> 28:39.728
FRED: We're trapped!
VELMA: Try the bookcase.

28:39.813 --> 28:40.404
What?

28:40.493 --> 28:43.053
One of these
has got to open a secret passageway!

28:43.133 --> 28:44.612
Velma, this is a ride!

28:44.693 --> 28:47.082
VELMA: You got a better plan, Fred?

28:51.213 --> 28:52.566
SCOOBY: What do we do?

28:52.653 --> 28:55.247
Do what we do best, Scoob! Eat!

28:59.293 --> 29:00.282
It's plastic!

29:00.373 --> 29:02.887
What do you care?
You drink out of a toilet!

29:03.733 --> 29:05.052
So do you!

29:06.533 --> 29:08.489
DAPHNE: I'm not helpless. I'm not helpless.

29:08.573 --> 29:10.484
I am helpless. I'm going to die!

29:30.253 --> 29:32.687
We made it, Scoob! We're alive!

29:37.853 --> 29:38.888
SHAGGY: That was weird.

29:39.933 --> 29:41.048
Fred?

29:41.773 --> 29:43.047
<i>Freddy? </i>

29:43.653 --> 29:45.052
Are you all right?

29:56.373 --> 29:57.852
VELMA: The last book.

30:01.373 --> 30:03.011
I don't feel so good.

30:03.493 --> 30:07.088
Reminds me of the time when we tried
to eat that guy in the hot dog costume.

30:08.053 --> 30:10.169
FRED: Looks like some kind of school.

30:10.373 --> 30:12.841
VELMA: In a spooky castle ride? Fishy.

30:14.293 --> 30:16.761
[Eerie instrumental music]

30:34.653 --> 30:36.450
INSTRUCTOR: <i>Welcome to America. </i>

30:37.093 --> 30:39.402
<i>I am using the language English. </i>

30:39.813 --> 30:42.168
SCOOBY: Shaggy, look.
SHAGGY: Let's check it out.

30:47.253 --> 30:51.451
Oh, boy. Lights, camera, action!
Huh, Scoob?

30:51.933 --> 30:53.810
INSTRUCTOR:
<i>Now that you're a young adult... </i>

30:54.333 --> 30:56.563
<i>... you'll need to learn societal do's... </i>

30:57.333 --> 30:58.482
<i>... and don'ts. </i>

30:59.453 --> 31:03.810
<i>Interaction between young people</i>
<i>is polite and casual. </i>

31:08.173 --> 31:09.526
<i>Sorry, bro. </i>

31:09.613 --> 31:12.081
<i>I will crush your bones into dust. </i>

31:15.653 --> 31:19.089
<i>Let's see how the situation</i>
<i>should be handled. </i>

31:19.173 --> 31:23.883
<i>Remember, today's young people</i>
<i>have a language all their own. </i>

31:27.373 --> 31:28.647
<i>Sorry, bro. </i>

31:28.733 --> 31:31.645
<i>No big whoop, dog. </i>
<i>Yo, did you catch that new vid on the box? </i>

31:31.733 --> 31:34.725
<i>True dat. </i>
<i>I'm up to snizzuff on all popular trends. </i>

31:35.133 --> 31:36.043
<i>Word. </i>

31:37.693 --> 31:40.890
It seems to be a brainwashing facility
of some type.

31:41.133 --> 31:43.044
VELMA: Wherever there's
a brainwashing cult...

31:43.133 --> 31:47.490
...there's always a power-hungry leader
behind it all. The Papa Smurf figure.

31:47.693 --> 31:49.126
Mondavarious.

31:49.653 --> 31:51.644
Then why would he have invited us here?

31:54.653 --> 31:55.642
[Ominous music]

32:18.053 --> 32:20.044
[Mysterious whispered chanting]

32:32.973 --> 32:34.042
[Daphne screams]

32:35.533 --> 32:37.808
[Triumphant music]

32:38.973 --> 32:39.962
Jellybeans.

32:40.053 --> 32:41.122
[Scooby burps]

32:43.893 --> 32:45.804
I'll have whatever he's having.

32:51.293 --> 32:52.806
Are you challenging me?

32:53.213 --> 32:54.407
[Gunslinging duel music]

32:54.893 --> 32:55.882
Maybe.

32:56.693 --> 32:58.490
[Scooby burps challengingly]

33:06.693 --> 33:08.684
Pull my finger. Too late!

33:15.173 --> 33:17.004
SHAGGY: You're in trouble.
SCOOBY: Oh, boy!

33:19.013 --> 33:21.083
[Shaggy farts powerfully]

33:30.613 --> 33:33.081
I'm not stopping until your fur is singed off.

33:42.973 --> 33:45.612
We're here to solve a mystery.

33:46.093 --> 33:47.003
Yes, Scoob.

33:51.293 --> 33:52.567
[Alarm sounds]

33:52.653 --> 33:54.052
Let's get out of here.

33:54.133 --> 33:55.725
[Dramatic instrumental music]

34:05.573 --> 34:07.131
I found a neat and scary clue.

34:07.213 --> 34:10.649
Us, too. We think this
is a brainwashing facility for an evil cult.

34:10.733 --> 34:13.610
Well, maybe this is the sacred relic thingy
they worship.

34:13.933 --> 34:17.164
SHAGGY: We're all gonna be relics
if we don't get out of here, man.

34:17.333 --> 34:18.732
FRED: I got a plan.

34:20.092 --> 34:22.004
ZARKOS: What's this smell?

34:25.893 --> 34:28.646
HENCHMAN: Sir, they found
the Daemon Ritus.

34:29.973 --> 34:32.771
ZARKOS: For your sake,
they better not have gone far.

34:34.172 --> 34:36.641
It is time to summon the big <i>muchachos</i>.

34:38.733 --> 34:40.212
SHAGGY: Oh, no!

34:40.853 --> 34:42.730
[Shaggy farts loudly]

34:46.612 --> 34:49.081
[Lively music]

35:07.333 --> 35:10.928
Mystery Inc. You all seem rather cheery.
Good news, I hope?

35:11.013 --> 35:13.925
- Mr. Mononucleosis.
- Yes?

35:14.013 --> 35:15.924
We have hit a clue smorgasbord.

35:17.253 --> 35:19.892
We have three suspects
as to who's behind this evil hoody.

35:20.413 --> 35:21.402
N'Goo Tauna.

35:21.493 --> 35:24.530
VELMA: <i>He believes your theme park's</i>
<i>been built on enchanted ground. </i>

35:24.613 --> 35:27.685
DAPHNE: <i>The Voodoo Man, who shrewdly</i>
<i>tricked me into going to the castle. </i>

35:28.533 --> 35:30.091
- And you.
- Me?

35:30.173 --> 35:33.085
FRED: Gang, let's split up.
We'll meet back here in a half hour.

35:33.173 --> 35:36.290
I'll interview employees,
see if they've noticed anything odd.

35:36.373 --> 35:39.729
I'm gonna get to work translating
these inscriptions that Daphne found.

35:39.813 --> 35:41.565
I'll go research cults on the Net.

35:45.373 --> 35:47.045
I'm a suspect?

35:47.173 --> 35:50.643
Don't take it personally.
It's mostly just because you creep me out.

35:50.733 --> 35:52.325
Oh, I see.

35:53.893 --> 35:54.769
Fine.

36:12.573 --> 36:13.562
VELMA: Jinkies.

36:13.773 --> 36:15.764
[Eerie instrumental music]

36:32.773 --> 36:34.968
Hey. Your friends ditch you?

36:36.293 --> 36:38.329
No, I always do the brain work.

36:40.133 --> 36:41.771
What's this?

36:42.253 --> 36:44.244
I believe it's called the Daemon Ritus.

36:44.333 --> 36:46.403
BOY: Daemon Ritus? What's it for?

36:46.493 --> 36:49.565
VELMA: I think this describes
a very old race of creatures.

36:49.893 --> 36:53.090
<i>These inscriptions are reminiscent</i>
<i>of ancient Pandamenous texts... </i>

36:53.173 --> 36:54.925
<i>... so I can make some of it out. </i>

36:55.013 --> 36:59.086
It looks like instructions
to some sort of secret ritual.

36:59.453 --> 37:02.047
VELMA: It is fascinating.
BARTENDER: On the house.

37:02.133 --> 37:03.122
<i>Nice sweater. </i>

37:03.213 --> 37:04.931
You really dig doing this, huh?

37:05.533 --> 37:07.603
<i>Like, clues and stuff. </i>

37:08.453 --> 37:12.731
Certainly. Really focusing
on a mystery reminds me of the old days.

37:15.253 --> 37:17.483
VELMA: <i>We were quite a crew back then. </i>

37:18.333 --> 37:20.085
<i>That was the best time of my life. </i>

37:20.853 --> 37:24.243
<i>Shaggy and Scooby. What goofballs! </i>

37:24.773 --> 37:26.365
<i>Kind of like they are today. </i>

37:28.333 --> 37:30.642
<i>And Daphne was so beautiful. </i>

37:31.213 --> 37:33.488
<i>She was the coolest girl at Coolsville High. </i>

37:34.373 --> 37:37.285
<i>Fred. He was so handsome. </i>

37:37.693 --> 37:39.684
<i>And he really knew how to accessorize. </i>

37:40.373 --> 37:41.567
BOY: <i>Sounds perfect. </i>

37:41.853 --> 37:45.163
VELMA: <i>Yeah, but every family has one nut. </i>

37:45.413 --> 37:47.722
Scrappy-dappy-doo!

37:47.813 --> 37:49.565
Ghosts don't stand a chance with me!

37:49.653 --> 37:53.248
Let me at them! I'll rack them!
I'll sock them!

37:53.413 --> 37:56.689
Scrappy, for the 1000th time,
there's no such thing as ghosts.

37:56.813 --> 37:57.723
Sure there are.

37:57.813 --> 38:02.728
And when I find them,
I'll give them a good dose of puppy power!

38:03.893 --> 38:06.202
Oh, God. He's peeing on me!

38:12.173 --> 38:14.971
VELMA: <i>That little egomaniac</i>
<i>had flipped his lid. </i>

38:15.333 --> 38:17.893
Scrappy, I told you.
No urinating on Daphne!

38:18.173 --> 38:20.767
- It was an accident.
- You were marking your territory!

38:20.933 --> 38:23.242
You don't have the scrote for this job, pally.

38:23.413 --> 38:28.441
Listen up, losers. The time has come that
you appoint me your unquestioned leader.

38:29.253 --> 38:31.323
Either that or I'm outta here!

38:34.493 --> 38:38.645
What's the idea? You can't do this to me!
People adore me!

38:40.693 --> 38:44.242
I'm as cute as a Powerpuff Girl!
I'll get my own TV show!

38:45.613 --> 38:46.887
Puppy power, huh?

38:46.973 --> 38:50.488
VELMA: And he wasn't even a puppy.
He had a gland disorder.

38:50.573 --> 38:52.052
[Laughing]

38:56.293 --> 38:57.772
[Whistling]

39:03.093 --> 39:04.162
[Screams] Yikes!

39:05.253 --> 39:07.528
SHAGGY: [Screams] Help me! Help me!
Monsters!

39:15.133 --> 39:18.011
Scooby, this is
the most embarrassing thing you've done...

39:18.093 --> 39:21.483
...since you decided to clean your beans
at Don Knotts' Christmas party.

39:22.573 --> 39:24.450
How many times do I have to tell you?

39:24.533 --> 39:29.004
There are no such things as ghouls,
ghosts, goblins, or monsters.

39:29.893 --> 39:32.646
Now listen up. There is absolutely...

39:32.733 --> 39:36.692
...absolutely no such thing as...

39:39.813 --> 39:42.247
[Yells] Monster!

39:45.333 --> 39:46.322
Fred!

39:48.853 --> 39:49.842
FRED: Scooby!

39:52.013 --> 39:53.446
Save Daphne!

39:59.253 --> 40:00.242
My glasses.

40:00.733 --> 40:02.405
<i>I can't find my glasses. </i>

40:02.573 --> 40:05.849
[Glass breaking]

40:06.173 --> 40:07.492
VELMA: I can't find my glasses.

40:10.093 --> 40:11.082
DEMON: Here we are.

40:12.413 --> 40:13.402
Thank you.

40:15.093 --> 40:17.323
Nice mask. Bad breath.

40:29.813 --> 40:30.802
Jinkies.

40:33.093 --> 40:34.412
Velma!

40:42.253 --> 40:43.242
BOY: Velma!

40:45.173 --> 40:47.926
This is, like, the opposite
of what I wanted to do today.

40:48.613 --> 40:50.410
[Chaotic instrumental music]

40:50.493 --> 40:51.482
[Beasts roaring]

41:05.653 --> 41:09.168
Stand back, sir! I'll protect you.

41:14.293 --> 41:15.646
Mr. Mondavarious!

41:18.653 --> 41:19.972
SHAGGY: Daphne, go!

41:22.733 --> 41:24.883
[Yells] Scooby Doo, where are you?

41:27.973 --> 41:30.851
[Loud funky music]

41:40.413 --> 41:44.452
SCOOBY:
Grammy's suitcase. Grammy's suitcase.

42:11.693 --> 42:12.682
Thank you.

42:14.773 --> 42:17.765
DAPHNE: Where's Scooby?
SHAGGY: I don't know. I hope he's okay.

42:18.173 --> 42:20.289
Right here. Scooby Dooby Doo!

42:29.733 --> 42:31.291
[Yell] Scooby!

43:11.413 --> 43:14.883
I have a sinking feeling these dudes
aren't brainwashed cult members.

43:15.693 --> 43:19.049
Then what are they? And what do they
want with the college students?

43:19.133 --> 43:20.725
We need to follow them.

43:20.813 --> 43:21.563
Say what?

43:21.653 --> 43:24.292
So we can defeat the creatures
and save Fred and Velma!

43:24.373 --> 43:26.125
Well, that's sort of like my plan.

43:26.213 --> 43:29.762
Which is: Get the heck out of here.
Let the creatures eat Fred and Velma!

43:29.853 --> 43:33.163
No way! Fred and Velma
always figured out everything.

43:33.293 --> 43:34.965
Now it's our turn, Shaggy.

43:35.053 --> 43:37.692
For the first time,
they're the damsels in distress.

43:37.893 --> 43:38.882
Not me.

43:41.333 --> 43:42.527
DAPHNE: Help?
SHAGGY: Timber.

43:51.053 --> 43:53.203
- Okay, I'm calling for help.
- No.

43:53.613 --> 43:56.127
No, I got this. I got this.

43:59.933 --> 44:01.286
I don't got this.

44:10.693 --> 44:11.967
Coast Guard, Fitzgibbon.

44:12.093 --> 44:14.891
Hello, sir. We're on Spooky Island.

44:15.373 --> 44:17.091
Our friends were...

44:18.133 --> 44:19.168
...kidnapped.

44:19.253 --> 44:21.084
MARY JANE: <i>We need someone here</i>
<i>right away! </i>

44:21.173 --> 44:25.644
Well, we do have a unit in the vicinity.
Can you meet them at the pier?

44:26.053 --> 44:27.691
They'll be right there.

44:31.453 --> 44:33.921
'<i>'</i> Our friends have been kidnapped. '<i>'</i>

44:35.533 --> 44:37.763
[Laughing evilly]

44:48.606 --> 44:52.076
[Suspenseful instrumental music]

45:03.366 --> 45:05.197
DAPHNE: Something messed up
is happening.

45:05.286 --> 45:07.242
Is the Coast Guard here?

45:07.926 --> 45:11.555
SHAGGY: What happened to the shattered
windows and the busted walls?

45:11.646 --> 45:14.114
Yo, Red. The ball.

45:17.286 --> 45:18.560
DAPHNE: Let's go.

45:19.646 --> 45:23.116
[Lively rock 'n' roll music]

45:33.086 --> 45:35.884
SHAGGY: Does anyone else think
this is strange?

45:37.606 --> 45:39.881
DAPHNE: Okay. We need to split up.
SHAGGY: Why?

45:40.606 --> 45:42.358
We still need to find Fred and Velma.

45:42.566 --> 45:45.160
- I'll go this way.
- And we'll go with you.

45:46.926 --> 45:48.439
Come on, Scoob.

46:22.246 --> 46:23.361
Fred?

46:23.446 --> 46:27.439
Yo, yo! The bee-atch was like, '<i>'</i> What? '<i>'</i>
And I was like, '<i>'</i> Later on! '<i>'</i>

46:30.166 --> 46:31.440
What up, dog?

46:31.526 --> 46:33.357
And dog.

46:33.766 --> 46:35.358
Keepin' it real.

46:35.766 --> 46:37.165
What happened last night?

46:37.246 --> 46:40.124
We got beats like it was the lizz nizz
on earth.

46:40.206 --> 46:42.674
FRED: Know what I'm saying, G?
SHAGGY: No.

46:45.046 --> 46:46.365
Do you hear that?

46:54.406 --> 46:55.680
Get the dog!

46:59.326 --> 47:01.044
ZARKOS: Damsel in distress.
DAPHNE: Let go of me!

47:01.126 --> 47:02.115
Help!

47:04.486 --> 47:05.965
SHAGGY: Hurry, get the door!

47:14.286 --> 47:17.756
SCOOBY: Why is Fred in a bad mood?
SHAGGY: He is not in a bad mood, Scoob!

47:18.206 --> 47:19.719
He is a monster!

47:28.886 --> 47:30.035
Shaggy, bikes!

47:30.566 --> 47:32.477
SHAGGY: I know, yikes!

47:32.846 --> 47:34.074
SCOOBY: No, bikes!

47:37.606 --> 47:39.881
[Revving bike engines]

47:49.366 --> 47:51.641
[Cheering and whooping]

47:55.886 --> 47:57.604
SCOOBY: Look out!

47:59.126 --> 48:02.084
[Gasps] I saw my friend.
There's something wrong with her eyes.

48:02.166 --> 48:03.394
Hop on!

48:16.566 --> 48:18.363
SHAGGY: What a drag!

48:30.326 --> 48:31.679
SHAGGY: Duck!

48:32.766 --> 48:35.155
[Ominous music]

48:39.646 --> 48:42.319
[Dramatic tribal beat]

48:48.646 --> 48:50.045
[Tires screeching]

48:52.526 --> 48:56.724
MARY JANE: That was great!
SHAGGY: Man, oh man, are you all right?

48:56.806 --> 48:58.558
SHAGGY: You were great.
MARY JANE: You, too.

48:58.646 --> 48:59.635
[Barking]

49:00.766 --> 49:02.597
What are you doing, man?

49:02.686 --> 49:04.961
Mary Jane is a man in a mask!

49:05.046 --> 49:07.401
- '<i>'</i> Mary Jane is a man in a mask? '<i>'</i>
- Scooby!

49:07.846 --> 49:11.236
SHAGGY: Dude, what are you doing, man?
Step off, Scoob.

49:11.326 --> 49:13.123
Shaggy, you're whipped!

49:13.206 --> 49:17.119
I'm whipped? Yeah?
Well, why don't you say that to my face?

49:17.206 --> 49:19.925
Okay, I will. Your mommy eats cat poop!

49:20.006 --> 49:22.804
No, Scooby Doo, your mom eats cat poop!

49:24.926 --> 49:27.565
You want some?
You want a little piece of the Shagster?

49:27.646 --> 49:29.477
Feel the pain, Scoob!

49:29.966 --> 49:32.082
SHAGGY: Come on! Two shots!

49:32.166 --> 49:34.077
<i>Me and you, me and you again. </i>

49:34.406 --> 49:36.522
SHAGGY: I'll give you something.

49:39.086 --> 49:40.075
[Shouts] Scoob!

49:41.326 --> 49:44.841
Scooby's been eaten. I gotta save him.
You stay here. I'll be right back.

49:44.926 --> 49:46.279
[Ghoul voice] No, Shaggy.

49:47.166 --> 49:49.316
I mean, it's too dangerous.

49:49.806 --> 49:52.445
I've got to. He's, like, my best pal.

49:54.526 --> 49:56.278
Friends don't quit.

49:56.966 --> 49:58.445
[Yelling]

50:08.566 --> 50:09.635
[Whispers] Scoob?

50:13.686 --> 50:14.960
SHAGGY: Scooby Doo.

50:16.006 --> 50:17.962
Where are you?

50:19.606 --> 50:20.595
Scoob!

50:40.486 --> 50:43.364
[Eerie instrumental music]

50:52.686 --> 50:55.246
VELMA: Shaggy! Shaggy!

50:57.126 --> 50:58.320
VELMA: Shaggy!

51:01.366 --> 51:02.515
Velma?

51:04.326 --> 51:05.805
SHAGGY: I'll save you.

51:13.766 --> 51:16.564
VELMA: Thanks, Shaggy.
Boy, am I glad to see you.

51:16.966 --> 51:20.515
Let me go so I can return to my body,
and then get out of here...

51:20.606 --> 51:23.962
...before they find you
and steal your protoplasm, too.

51:24.046 --> 51:27.243
VELMA:
I always knew you were a hero, Shaggy.

51:29.126 --> 51:31.003
VELMA: [Yells] Jinkies!

51:38.046 --> 51:39.718
[Ghoul screaming]

51:48.086 --> 51:49.360
[Screaming]

52:02.046 --> 52:05.038
SHAGGY: Hey, buddy.
FRED: Shaggy. Listen, man.

52:05.246 --> 52:09.125
Someone must have spiked my root beer
last night. Talk me down, man!

52:09.206 --> 52:10.639
Talk me down!

52:10.726 --> 52:13.718
Fred, you're a frigging protoplasmic head.

52:16.006 --> 52:17.200
I know.

52:17.966 --> 52:21.515
But I'm still the best-looking
protoplasmic head here.

52:24.366 --> 52:25.845
FRED: How do you drive this thing?

52:25.926 --> 52:29.885
FAKE FRED: The Darkopolypse is upon us.
Gather what you need for the ceremony.

52:29.966 --> 52:31.922
FRED: On your right. The left.

52:33.086 --> 52:35.281
FRED: I'm coming, good-looking!

52:38.606 --> 52:41.120
Thank you so much! You've saved me!
Thank you!

52:41.206 --> 52:43.674
Sorry, I'm looking for my friends.

52:49.406 --> 52:52.557
Put me back, Shaggy.
I'll figure a way out myself.

52:52.646 --> 52:54.796
- Like, how?
- I don't know.

52:55.846 --> 52:58.314
I'll use my tongue as an oar
and swim to the edge.

52:58.406 --> 52:59.725
Sorry.

53:10.006 --> 53:12.076
[Eerie instrumental music]

53:14.966 --> 53:16.558
VELMA: Yo, yo, you, yo.

53:41.486 --> 53:43.681
You could use a little sunlight.

53:56.526 --> 53:58.756
VELMA: That's one part
of the mystery solved.

53:58.846 --> 54:02.475
The creatures must need our bodies
to survive in sunlight.

54:03.126 --> 54:04.798
Like a human suit.

54:05.206 --> 54:07.800
SPF 1,000,000.

54:09.246 --> 54:12.158
But what are they doing here
in the first place?

54:14.286 --> 54:15.924
Daphne, you okay?

54:17.366 --> 54:18.481
FRED'S SOUL: Yeah.

54:19.006 --> 54:20.724
FRED'S SOUL: But I'm not Daphne!

54:21.046 --> 54:22.161
Fred?

54:28.606 --> 54:32.360
FRED'S SOUL: I couldn't get to my body.
I didn't know where else to go. I panicked!

54:32.446 --> 54:35.483
FRED'S SOUL: It's not easy to steer
when you're pure spirit.

54:38.966 --> 54:41.036
FRED'S SOUL: I can look at myself naked.

54:41.686 --> 54:43.085
Oh, brother.

54:51.366 --> 54:53.800
DAPHNE'S SOUL: Get your hands off me.
VELMA: Daphne?

54:53.886 --> 54:56.116
DAPHNE'S SOUL: He planned this
somehow. Didn't he?

54:56.446 --> 54:58.084
FRED'S SOUL: Hey, good-looking.

54:59.766 --> 55:02.326
DAPHNE'S SOUL: Fred! You egocentric...

55:02.526 --> 55:05.199
SHAGGY: Tell me you guys are you.
DAPHNE'S SOUL: Fred keeps touching me.

55:05.286 --> 55:08.642
VELMA: Kind of makes you nostalgic
for the homicidal creatures, doesn't it?

55:08.726 --> 55:11.286
SHAGGY: I stole this. I hope it helps.

55:11.526 --> 55:13.164
VELMA: The Daemon Ritus.

55:19.606 --> 55:21.039
DAPHNE: I'm me again.

55:21.206 --> 55:22.605
VELMA'S SOUL: Yippee for you.

55:22.726 --> 55:25.923
SHAGGY'S SOUL: Man, like,
why am I wearing a dress?

55:26.006 --> 55:29.794
FRED'S SOUL: Everyone remain calm.
Velma, what the heck's going on?

55:29.926 --> 55:31.996
VELMA'S SOUL: If my calculations
are correct...

55:32.086 --> 55:36.045
<i>... due to the unstable nature of protoplasm</i>
<i>in proximity of the Daemon Ritus... </i>

55:36.126 --> 55:40.244
VELMA'S SOUL: we're simply going to
continue randomly changing bodies until...

55:44.126 --> 55:47.277
VELMA'S SOUL: Until the protoplasm
realigns with the appropriate body.

55:47.366 --> 55:48.685
DAPHNE'S SOUL: I'm Fred again!

55:48.766 --> 55:53.317
SHAGGY'S SOUL: Daph, what's wrong
with you? Don't you ever eat?

55:59.126 --> 56:00.115
FRED: I'm me!

56:00.206 --> 56:01.195
DAPHNE: I'm back!

56:01.286 --> 56:03.356
SHAGGY: Like, me too!
VELMA: Told you so!

56:06.046 --> 56:08.116
DAPHNE: Oh, no!
VELMA: Let's go.

56:11.286 --> 56:14.358
Something tells me
that was the wrong ingredient.

56:14.446 --> 56:15.561
Wait!

56:16.166 --> 56:18.396
I know how to handle this guy.

56:18.526 --> 56:19.276
Hey, you!

56:19.606 --> 56:21.119
What are you doing?

56:21.206 --> 56:23.845
Yes. That is masterful.

56:24.126 --> 56:28.278
I'm trying to do a voodoo ritual.
It's important to get the right ingredients.

56:28.366 --> 56:32.279
The only way I can protect myself
is by blessing this dead Arnouki beast.

56:32.366 --> 56:33.355
<i>I'll tell you something. </i>

56:33.446 --> 56:36.882
I got a feeling they're about
to perform their evil Darkopolypse ritual.

56:36.966 --> 56:39.275
VELMA: Darkopolypse ritual?
VOODOO MAN: That's right.

56:39.366 --> 56:41.322
That's what the ancient text describes.

56:41.406 --> 56:42.680
Hold it! Don't open it!

56:42.766 --> 56:46.236
VELMA: They use the protoplasm in the vat
as an energy source.

56:47.246 --> 56:51.683
And the leader needs to absorb
a purely good soul to complete the ritual.

56:51.766 --> 56:54.917
Legend has it, once the Darkopolypse ritual
is performed...

56:55.006 --> 56:58.635
...the creatures will rule all Earth
for 10,000 years.

56:58.886 --> 57:02.322
So I'm bringing this Arnouki
beast up in my house to protect myself.

57:02.406 --> 57:04.715
Do you have another one of those?

57:04.806 --> 57:09.004
DAPHNE: Those creatures are taking
over the world? That is so mean!

57:09.086 --> 57:12.237
Now, they can't do the ritual
without a pure human soul.

57:12.326 --> 57:14.078
Where will they get one of those?

57:14.166 --> 57:15.884
I didn't say human.

57:17.566 --> 57:18.794
Oh, boy.

57:19.166 --> 57:20.645
[Whimpering]

57:36.166 --> 57:37.360
Hello, puppy.

57:38.806 --> 57:41.878
So, if the person behind all this needs
Scooby Doo...

57:41.966 --> 57:45.003
Then that person is the one
who brought Scooby here.

57:49.406 --> 57:50.680
Scoobert!

57:50.766 --> 57:54.042
How are you, my friend? Sit down. Please.

57:54.286 --> 57:55.401
Okay.

57:58.166 --> 57:59.485
EMILE: Scooby Snack?

57:59.566 --> 58:00.885
Maybe one.

58:05.686 --> 58:08.075
We'll need some more of those.

58:09.406 --> 58:10.919
That's me!

58:11.326 --> 58:15.319
It certainly is. And that's because, why?

58:16.046 --> 58:18.480
We love you, Scooby Doo.

58:19.606 --> 58:23.724
Unlike that alleged friend of yours, Shaggy.

58:24.286 --> 58:25.639
<i>He wouldn't believe you... </i>

58:25.726 --> 58:29.435
...about that nasty girl Mary Jane,
would he?

58:30.286 --> 58:31.321
No.

58:32.766 --> 58:34.961
But I believe you, my friend.

58:35.606 --> 58:39.838
And that's why
I've got a very important job for you.

58:40.046 --> 58:41.445
What's that?

58:42.126 --> 58:45.641
That's a cat with a bobbing head.
Please don't touch it.

58:46.006 --> 58:46.995
Scooby...

58:47.606 --> 58:49.403
...I would like you...

58:49.806 --> 58:53.321
...to be a sacrifice.

58:53.766 --> 58:55.245
A sacrifice?

58:59.686 --> 59:02.883
If Mondorajagaga wanted Scooby,
why'd he invite the rest of us?

59:02.966 --> 59:06.038
It doesn't matter.
We gotta, like, go save Scoob.

59:06.126 --> 59:10.005
Shag, our area of expertise
is nut jobs in Halloween costumes.

59:10.086 --> 59:12.236
We're supposed to be heroes, man.

59:13.806 --> 59:16.366
So I'm going to do what I always do.

59:16.726 --> 59:21.163
I'm going to eat myself a Scooby Snack
and I'm going to save my best pal.

59:23.486 --> 59:24.760
FRED: Velmster?

59:25.606 --> 59:28.200
You think I'm going to fall for that?

59:28.766 --> 59:30.757
Giving me my own nickname?

59:30.846 --> 59:33.076
Trying to make me feel like...

59:34.126 --> 59:35.878
...part of the gang?

59:38.606 --> 59:40.403
We could make a plan.

59:40.686 --> 59:44.474
What can I do? The only thing I'm good for
is getting caught.

59:44.846 --> 59:47.360
But you never let that stop you before.

59:47.446 --> 59:51.041
And if that's not a true hero,
then I don't know what is.

01:00:00.526 --> 01:00:02.721
Let's get jinky with it.

01:00:05.606 --> 01:00:07.881
[Funky rock 'n' roll music]

01:00:35.526 --> 01:00:38.563
Okay, so, we use the pulleys
to tip over the vat.

01:00:38.646 --> 01:00:42.639
VELMA: Daphne, open the air vents from
the outside and release the disco skull.

01:00:42.726 --> 01:00:44.603
The light will refract off the skull...

01:00:44.686 --> 01:00:49.362
The creatures will explode, I'll find Scoob
and we will have saved the world.

01:00:50.686 --> 01:00:53.154
FRED: Oh, no. The ritual's beginning.

01:00:53.686 --> 01:00:56.075
DAPHNE: Quick!
VELMA: Shaggy, attach this to the vat!

01:01:05.126 --> 01:01:06.718
We're here to save you!

01:01:06.806 --> 01:01:08.319
VELMA: Shaggy, faster!

01:01:08.726 --> 01:01:09.761
All systems go!

01:01:11.046 --> 01:01:12.274
Wait, no!

01:01:12.366 --> 01:01:14.675
Mystery Inc rides again.

01:01:41.526 --> 01:01:42.845
[Beating of drums]

01:01:42.926 --> 01:01:44.757
VELMA: Quick! Hide the Daemon Ritus!

01:01:57.086 --> 01:01:59.202
WOMAN:
Would you like another Scooby Snack?

01:02:00.006 --> 01:02:01.359
Okay.

01:02:01.846 --> 01:02:03.199
Scooby Doo!

01:02:06.686 --> 01:02:08.756
[Chanting to tribal music]

01:02:35.646 --> 01:02:36.920
[Whimpering]

01:03:08.206 --> 01:03:10.083
[Fred mumbles]

01:03:17.526 --> 01:03:18.754
Yo, yo, yo.

01:03:19.086 --> 01:03:20.519
FRED: Yo, homedogs!

01:03:21.166 --> 01:03:23.282
<i>Y'all forgot the next part of the dance... </i>

01:03:23.366 --> 01:03:26.483
...where we do the electric slide,
where, you know...

01:03:26.566 --> 01:03:27.794
It's electric.

01:03:28.286 --> 01:03:29.275
[Fred cheers]

01:03:29.366 --> 01:03:32.517
FRED: And back it on up and drive the bus...

01:03:32.606 --> 01:03:34.005
...and stop.

01:03:34.286 --> 01:03:35.514
<i>And back it up. </i>

01:03:35.606 --> 01:03:38.120
<i>And back it on up. Hurry up, Velma. </i>

01:03:38.286 --> 01:03:39.878
EMILE: Fred! Velma!

01:03:39.966 --> 01:03:43.754
Welcome to my little
'<i>'</i> End of the World'<i>'</i> party.

01:03:44.046 --> 01:03:46.799
<i>I've waited a long time for this moment. </i>

01:03:47.086 --> 01:03:51.204
<i>Thank you for returning</i>
<i>the ultimate party favor... </i>

01:03:51.806 --> 01:03:53.603
...the Daemon Ritus.

01:03:56.206 --> 01:04:00.119
EMILE: And now, behold the sacrifice.

01:04:02.246 --> 01:04:04.635
Thank you. Thank you.

01:04:05.486 --> 01:04:07.158
Hello, thank you.

01:04:09.726 --> 01:04:11.557
Thank you. Shaggy?

01:04:15.086 --> 01:04:17.839
Let's run for it.
We, like, gotta get out of here.

01:04:17.926 --> 01:04:19.996
I'm a sacrifice, you know.

01:04:20.086 --> 01:04:23.044
A sacrifice? That's not a good thing, Scoob.

01:04:28.806 --> 01:04:30.637
I'm sorry I yelled at you.

01:04:30.726 --> 01:04:34.036
I'm really sorry I haven't been
a very good friend since we got here.

01:04:34.126 --> 01:04:36.924
But listen to me, bro,
you gotta trust me now.

01:04:37.006 --> 01:04:39.964
- You don't trust me!
- I do trust you, Scoob.

01:04:40.366 --> 01:04:43.881
Now, look. Who's your best buddy?

01:04:45.286 --> 01:04:46.765
SCOOBY: Shaggy.
SHAGGY: That's right.

01:04:46.846 --> 01:04:49.758
- Who's my best buddy in the whole world?
- Scooby Doo?

01:04:49.846 --> 01:04:51.120
SHAGGY: That's right.

01:04:51.206 --> 01:04:55.199
You are. And we're, like, two trippy peas
in a far-out pod, man!

01:04:56.846 --> 01:05:00.361
<i>And best buddies, they trust each other. </i>
<i>So let's do what we do best. </i>

01:05:00.446 --> 01:05:04.325
Let's run out of here, screaming in fear
like a couple of lunatics, okay?

01:05:04.406 --> 01:05:05.156
Okay.

01:05:05.246 --> 01:05:08.238
On the count of... Let's make it five. One...

01:05:08.846 --> 01:05:10.165
...two...

01:05:10.766 --> 01:05:12.119
Scooby Doo!

01:05:18.006 --> 01:05:19.678
SCOOBY'S SOUL: Hey, look at me!

01:05:30.006 --> 01:05:31.837
EMILE: The moment is at hand.

01:05:32.606 --> 01:05:37.157
<i>Through the Daemon Ritus, </i>
<i>I shall absorb the energy source. </i>

01:05:46.446 --> 01:05:47.799
<i>And now... </i>

01:05:47.926 --> 01:05:50.360
...to complete the transformation...

01:05:50.446 --> 01:05:53.518
...I shall absorb the Pure One!

01:05:53.646 --> 01:05:54.635
Scoob!

01:05:55.486 --> 01:05:59.240
Ultimate power shall be mine!

01:05:59.806 --> 01:06:01.637
Nobody absorbs my pal!

01:06:05.086 --> 01:06:06.314
SCOOBY: Quick!

01:06:20.286 --> 01:06:21.639
I'm free!

01:06:23.526 --> 01:06:24.879
Look at me!

01:06:29.086 --> 01:06:31.361
Come on, let's get the Daemon Ritus!

01:06:31.446 --> 01:06:34.916
ZARKOS: Get off my swingset!

01:06:41.406 --> 01:06:42.885
Cowabunga!

01:06:48.726 --> 01:06:50.125
Look, Velms.

01:06:50.606 --> 01:06:52.198
A man in a mask.

01:06:57.486 --> 01:07:01.115
We love you, Scooby Doo. We love you...

01:07:02.606 --> 01:07:05.678
That alleged friend of yours, Shaggy.

01:07:05.766 --> 01:07:07.438
I shall absorb...

01:07:10.686 --> 01:07:14.235
Puppy power! I've outsmarted...

01:07:17.326 --> 01:07:19.635
VELMA: Scrappy Doo.
SCRAPPY: Correction.

01:07:19.766 --> 01:07:22.599
The new, improved Scrappy.

01:07:22.766 --> 01:07:27.157
Because I, Scrappy Dappy Doo,
have absorbed enough energy to...

01:07:28.926 --> 01:07:32.999
To rule the world
with my all-powerful army!

01:07:35.006 --> 01:07:39.682
And I've brought you here, puny,
pathetic Mystery Inc...

01:07:40.086 --> 01:07:43.522
...to witness my moment of triumph.

01:07:44.206 --> 01:07:49.234
All I need to complete
my transformation is Scooby Doo.

01:07:51.406 --> 01:07:52.919
Don't you mean Melvin Doo?

01:07:53.606 --> 01:07:55.164
Seize them!

01:07:55.446 --> 01:07:57.596
Like, let's get out of here!

01:07:59.006 --> 01:08:00.962
SCRAPPY: Take that, pretty boy!

01:08:17.246 --> 01:08:19.555
SHAGGY: This is totally ungroovy, Scoob!

01:08:20.046 --> 01:08:23.834
Scooby Doo, where are you?

01:08:26.845 --> 01:08:28.120
<i>Señorita</i>.

01:08:28.206 --> 01:08:31.676
[Loud rock music]

01:08:39.246 --> 01:08:43.205
SCRAPPY: Yield to my puppy power!

01:08:43.765 --> 01:08:45.721
VELMA: We have to tip over
the protoplasm vat.

01:08:45.886 --> 01:08:48.319
FRED: How?
VELMA: The pincer! Come on!

01:08:48.406 --> 01:08:51.876
[Rock version of <i>Scooby Doo</i> theme song]

01:08:53.566 --> 01:08:57.604
You all need to step back,
because Fredster's got his groove on.

01:09:08.886 --> 01:09:09.955
[Daphne grunts]

01:09:14.446 --> 01:09:15.515
[Zarkos whines]

01:09:16.126 --> 01:09:18.799
Gotcha! You look so much bigger on TV!

01:09:45.046 --> 01:09:47.765
SCRAPPY: Come back here,
you lazy beatnik!

01:09:52.326 --> 01:09:55.443
Oh, crud!

01:09:55.686 --> 01:09:57.085
Told you so!

01:10:02.366 --> 01:10:03.879
Like, wow!

01:10:04.726 --> 01:10:06.478
Give me the dog!

01:10:08.406 --> 01:10:09.555
SCOOBY: Scrappy!

01:10:09.646 --> 01:10:11.841
Down! Sit! Bad Scrappy!

01:10:21.126 --> 01:10:24.402
Let's finish this puppy! Now!

01:10:24.806 --> 01:10:27.001
Oh, no! Not again!

01:10:27.566 --> 01:10:29.602
Captured again, <i>señorita</i> ?

01:10:30.446 --> 01:10:32.960
Not this time!

01:10:51.406 --> 01:10:53.317
Now who's the damsel in distress?

01:10:53.406 --> 01:10:55.795
- Me?
- Straight up.

01:11:30.966 --> 01:11:34.083
SCRAPPY: Mystery Inc, this ain't over!

01:11:34.366 --> 01:11:36.197
<i>Not by a long shot! </i>

01:11:38.286 --> 01:11:40.880
<i>I'll rock you and sock you... </i>

01:11:40.966 --> 01:11:43.196
...and crush you like...

01:11:45.246 --> 01:11:46.395
Like, dude.

01:11:46.526 --> 01:11:49.802
SCRAPPY: What?
SHAGGY: You're a bad puppy!

01:12:05.126 --> 01:12:07.720
I can still take you!
Put them up, you mangy mutt!

01:12:08.686 --> 01:12:10.085
Is that all you got?

01:12:15.726 --> 01:12:17.796
[Cheering]

01:12:25.406 --> 01:12:26.805
FRED: Hey, Daph!

01:12:28.446 --> 01:12:30.437
- We did it!
- Yes, we did.

01:12:40.606 --> 01:12:41.595
Oh, Fred!

01:12:42.126 --> 01:12:43.479
Cut it out!

01:12:59.006 --> 01:13:00.917
Mr. Mondavarious, is that you?

01:13:01.006 --> 01:13:01.995
Yes.

01:13:02.286 --> 01:13:03.639
Thank goodness!

01:13:03.726 --> 01:13:05.000
Thank you! Thank you!

01:13:05.086 --> 01:13:06.405
BOY: Thank you!

01:13:12.606 --> 01:13:14.801
You're fogging up my glasses.

01:13:18.166 --> 01:13:20.600
Two years ago, that little pest...

01:13:20.806 --> 01:13:23.957
...turns up at a casting session
for our evil elves.

01:13:24.046 --> 01:13:25.877
<i>Next, I'm stuck in a hole... </i>

01:13:25.966 --> 01:13:29.641
...and he's cavorting about
in a mechanical version of me.

01:13:30.246 --> 01:13:32.635
<i>But look, thank you so much! </i>

01:13:35.566 --> 01:13:37.318
What a delight! Fantastic!

01:13:37.406 --> 01:13:38.805
<i>Fantastic! </i>

01:13:40.606 --> 01:13:42.039
Shaggy!

01:13:42.126 --> 01:13:43.115
Scooby Doo!

01:13:46.206 --> 01:13:47.878
[Laughing]

01:13:49.526 --> 01:13:52.916
- I love you, Shaggy.
- I love you, too, Scoob.

01:13:53.206 --> 01:13:55.242
Now, get off me, buddy.

01:13:59.246 --> 01:14:00.440
Thanks.

01:14:00.606 --> 01:14:02.278
You saved my life.

01:14:02.726 --> 01:14:04.364
No problem.

01:14:12.766 --> 01:14:14.802
And thank you, Scooby Doo.

01:14:15.286 --> 01:14:17.356
MARY JANE: My little
schmookem wookem.

01:14:17.446 --> 01:14:18.435
Shucks!

01:14:29.646 --> 01:14:31.716
[Screaming and cheering]

01:14:43.126 --> 01:14:45.401
Fred, can you tell us
how you solved the case?

01:14:45.726 --> 01:14:46.761
FRED: Yes.

01:14:46.846 --> 01:14:50.441
It all started when I was giving
a speech on my new book and...

01:14:55.006 --> 01:14:58.078
I really think the Velmster
should take it from here.

01:15:00.046 --> 01:15:01.081
[Whispers] Go.

01:15:05.446 --> 01:15:09.325
Through the combined intuitive powers
of Mystery Inc...

01:15:09.606 --> 01:15:12.962
<i>... we've discovered</i>
<i>the real villain behind this mystery... </i>

01:15:13.046 --> 01:15:15.640
...is, in fact, Scrappy Cornelius Doo...

01:15:15.766 --> 01:15:19.156
<i>... who, sadly, was corrupted</i>
<i>by the power of the Daemon Ritus. </i>

01:15:19.246 --> 01:15:21.760
SCRAPPY: Get over it!
So, I got a little cranky!

01:15:21.846 --> 01:15:25.680
Scrap, it's no reason to freak out like
a jerk and try to kill all of humanity.

01:15:25.766 --> 01:15:29.918
I would've gotten away with it, too,
if not for you meddling sons of...

01:15:30.006 --> 01:15:32.156
Now that Mystery Inc is back together...

01:15:32.246 --> 01:15:35.477
...do you have any comment on the
Mud Bog Ghoul terrorizing London?

01:15:35.566 --> 01:15:37.318
Whatever the case...

01:15:37.566 --> 01:15:40.126
...Mystery Inc will be there.
- Solving mysteries, man.

01:15:40.446 --> 01:15:43.677
DAPHNE: Righting wrongs.
VELMA: Looking for clues and kicking butt.

01:15:59.646 --> 01:16:01.318
[Rap music plays]

01:16:01.406 --> 01:16:03.715
SHAGGY: <i>How groovy is this, man? </i>

01:16:03.806 --> 01:16:07.685
Spooky Island finally came through
with its all-you-can-eat deal.

01:16:07.926 --> 01:16:12.238
And there's nobody I'd rather
gorge myself with than you, Scooby Doo.

01:16:13.326 --> 01:16:14.918
My best friend.

01:16:15.006 --> 01:16:16.519
You're my best friend, buddy.

01:16:16.726 --> 01:16:19.559
You're beautiful
like a beautiful piece of pizza!

01:16:25.286 --> 01:16:26.275
Zoinks!

01:16:26.526 --> 01:16:29.279
Them peppers is, like, hot!

01:16:29.646 --> 01:16:32.558
- Wimp!
- Wimp? You think you can handle it?

01:16:32.966 --> 01:16:36.038
Why don't you put your mouth
where your mouth is!

01:16:40.286 --> 01:16:41.275
Okay!

01:16:47.966 --> 01:16:49.445
[Panting]

01:16:50.926 --> 01:16:51.915
SHAGGY: Scooby Doo.

01:16:52.606 --> 01:16:53.834
<i>Are you feeling okay? </i>

01:16:57.006 --> 01:16:58.598
[Yells] Oh no!

01:17:10.366 --> 01:17:11.640
Here you go, Scoob!

01:17:20.246 --> 01:17:23.158
- How did that taste, man?
- Delicious!

01:17:23.366 --> 01:17:25.755
Well, <i>garçon</i>, let's get two more!

01:17:30.886 --> 01:17:32.160
On the count of three.

01:17:32.366 --> 01:17:33.162
One!

01:17:33.646 --> 01:17:34.635
Two!

01:17:35.206 --> 01:17:36.355
Three!

01:17:36.446 --> 01:17:38.323
[Screaming]

01:17:40.406 --> 01:17:43.876
[Rap music]

